<dl id="n01029a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01029a">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01029a"> 29(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the worse for drink <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n01029a"><li>FW 176.31 </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/lexg.htm#n01029a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/l39g.htm#n01029a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n01029a">MS BL 47471b-51v</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:334 <a name="g10d" href="../../ff/fdra/gda.htm#g10d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/g/g10d.htm#n01029a">Draft: I.7&sect;1.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[CURRENT TOPICS]</font> <font color="green">[on &lsquo;the drink evil&rsquo;]</font>: I am informed that publicans have gone so far as to hold all-night dances on or near their premises, and the poor fellows <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> make their way home as best they can in the small hours of the morning much <mark>the worse of drink</mark>; 319/2: a sergeant <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> sent one of his constables to one village, for three Sundays running, with instructions that he should see that the licensing laws were observed. On each Sunday of the three the constable arrived back at the barrack the worse of drink! <small> <a name="TL11nov22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TL11nov22"><cite title="source">The Leader</cite></a> (11 November 1922) 319/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: &lsquo;CURRENT TOPICS&rsquo;: each issue opens with this &mdash; a series of editorial comments on topical themes. </mm> </dd></dl>
